It is designed to help parents give their children a feeling of security and confidence so their children explore, learn, grow and build positive relationships.<br /><br />Connections, a Project Harmony program, works with schools and health care professionals to identify children in grades K-8 in need of mental health services.  Focuses on children who are not receiving child welfare or juvenile justice services.
